properties.Name: EEZ
properties.Description: Taiwan (the Republic of China) claims a 200 nautical mile exclusive economic zone (EEZ) and has not delimited the boundaries of this zone with any of its neighbors. Our EEZ representation shows a 200 nm buffer for areas where the distance between Taiwan and its neighbors is greater than 400 nm, and in all other cases uses median lines.  Our representation also includes a hypothetical EEZ from Pratas Island drawn using equidistant points with the Philippine and Chinese coasts. Taiwan has also published the limits of a unilateral provisional EEZ enforcement area, the boundary for which can be found in our Agreements and Claims layer.
